data.name: volBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Volatility: All the "Move" values added up. This helps to gauge the market at a quick glance. Different intervals will have different ranges in volatility. A 3 minute interval might only reach "30" as it's highest number reached, while a 4 hour interval could equal "200".
Observing this number, and learning it's tricks, can be the key to finding a winning strategy.

data.name: intervalBox.ToolTip
data.value:
How often the "Past Price" will be updated.
The past price is how BSFX determines what the move is. The lower the interval, the more frequent the price update, the higher the interval, the less frequesnt the price updates. If you would like fast short moves, go for a lower interval. Long steady moves, go for a higher interval.

data.name: netPL.ToolTip
data.value: Day P/L includes the profit and loss for the day’s trading session from 17:00 New York Time. This will display only the trading activity, no deposits and withdrawals. This is a great risk management tool to allow you to keep track of your trading session profits without having to run reports.

data.name: allocatedFundsBox.ToolTip
data.value: This is the amount of account equity currently committed to maintain open positions. Used Margin can be thought of as the trader’s deposit on the open position. The account must maintain AT LEAST this amount for open trades to remain open.

data.name: accountLevBox.ToolTip
data.value: This is the “floating” value of funds in the account, including profits and losses on open positions. If you were to close all open positions, the account’s Equity would become the account’s Balance, as this “floating” value would then be “locked in.”
